title: For Sale:  223/556 AR w/Strikefire II
postcontent: I dont want to sell this rifle, but I've had an expense pop up and I could use the money. It's a custom rifle that was purchased new from another individual. It was pre-built, I just bought it. It's a complete Anderson lower. The upper is a forging made of 7075 T6, hard coat anodized. The BCG was identified by my FFL as a Daniel Defense full auto. Barrel is 16" 4150 Chrome MolyVanadium with a 1 in 9 twist rate. Feed ramp is M4, and the rifle has a flat top upper. 10" free-floating keymod handguard. Also included is a generic grip-pod, 2 polymer magazines, a set of FieldSport flip-up iron sights and a Vortex Strikefire II red/green dot with 4 MOA dot. The case is a pluck and pull Plano all-weather case. Has 5 latches to keep it secured closed, it's waterproof and is said to float (I'm not sure how much weight can be in the case before it loses buoyancy). This case is TSA approved.  I usually use one-piece cleaning rods, but I have an extra unopened Hoppes cleaning set for 22 caliber firearms. These rifles usually sell for around $650. Case was $70, grip-pod was $25 the mags are $25 for the pair, BUIS were about $30, and the Strikefire II is $180.  That brings the total to about $980 here. Id like to see $800 for the lot, price is a bit negotiable, but I won't dip too low on it. It's a good rifle with a good setup. I've put about 550 rounds though it with zero failures of any sort. As far as accuracy goes, it's a red dot, so accuracy will suffer over range. 100 yards, it can shoot about 7", 50 yards, about 2.5-3".  I'm by no means an expert with an AR with a red dot, I'm more into bolt guns. I'm sure someone more experienced with the platform can get better results.

postcontent: This is about as rare of a gun as I have seen for sale. Extremely low production run and mint condition. A verifiable 1 of 250-350 run of one of a kind Colt. Here is the lowdown as far as I know it: Colt 1911 model- Special Edition (1989) -COLT TANK OFFICERS ACP (Special Edition) Caliber: .45acp Barrel Length: 3.5" Finish: Matte BluePrice:  $2,000 It was apparently a special run of pistols from Colt. These are limited run, Special Edition, Colt 1911s. Without a doubt one of 350 and arguably 250 ever built. If you do some research you will see the exact number of examples produced is not really known.  This one is absolutey in perfect condtion. It boasts the following special features; An officers ACP slide assembly, a Combat Commander receiver assembly, a flat mainspring housing with lanyard loop, a beveled magazine well, a serrated front strap, and a 3-Dot sighting system. Each pistol also features the special rollmark "TANK OFFICERS" on the left side of the slide. If you happen to be a Colt colletor you will be very hard pressed to find a more rare example of a 1911. To most collectors this would undoubtedly be a Grail gun. This one displays in perfect condtition, no flaws and original. Gun only, no original box or paperwork. This one should speak for itself. All completely original and as advertiesed. This is a hard gun to part with.
